    "recap_url": "https://www.upstatespartans.com/news/2026/3/22/trey-bentleys-career-day-headlined-by-his-first-collegiate-homer-leads-baseball-in-series-finale-at-longwood",
    "recap_headline": "University of South Carolina Upstate Athletics",
    "recap_text": "FARMVILLE, Va. \u2013\nLooking to win its second straight series to begin Big South Conference play, USC Upstate baseball saw its latest comeback attempt fall just short as it looked to erase the deficit late in a 12-11 setback Sunday at Longwood.\nThe highest-scoring game of the weekend saw the sides trade jabs throughout the afternoon with Upstate pouncing for four runs in the first inning before adding two more in the third to build a 6-1 advantage. The Lancers, however, methodically chipped away at the lead before wrestling it away in the fifth before extending it to five runs in the sixth. From there, the Spartans began their rally with a run in the seventh, two in the eighth, and one in the ninth, falling just short in the final frame.\nRedshirt freshman leftfielder\nTrey Bentley\nthe second multi-RBI game of his career, driving home a career-best three runs behind a career-high-tying two hits, both extra-base hits, including his first collegiate home run. Joining him with a multi-hit and multi-RBI effort, redshirt sophomore centerfielder\nHenry Zenor\ncollected two hits and two RBI while senior first baseman\nPreston Lucas\ntallied three hits.\nGame Information\nScore: Longwood 12; USC Upstate 11\nRecords: USC Upstate (12-13; 3-3 Big South); Longwood (17-7; 3-3 Big South)\nLocation: Buddy Bolding Stadium | Farmville, Va.\nHow It Happened\nT1: Striking in the opening frame for the first time this weekend, Upstate used three doubles to score four runs in the stanza.\nTyler Lang\nfollowed a\nHenry Zenor\ndouble to plate the first tally before later scoring on a\nMaloy Heaghney\nsingle to right-center. An RBI groundout from\nJake Armsey\npushed across run three before\nPreston Lucas\ndoubled home the final run.\nB2: Getting a run back, Longwood's Tre Keels hit a solo shot to left.\nT3: Answering the Lancers' run and then some,\nTrey Bentley\nlaunched his first career homer into the trees in right-center, plating two more runs for the Spartans.\nB3: Pulling themselves closer, the Lancers scratched three runs in the frame, the biggest hit a two-run homer from Brogan Jones.\nB4: Drawing closer, Longwood added another tally on a fielder's choice with Upstate attempting to turn two with runners on the corner.\nB5: Taking the lead, the Lancers scored twice on a two-run home run to center from Lucas Johnson.\nT6: Battling back to knot the game, Zenor followed a\nGage Griggs\ndouble with a single ripped through the right side, allowing Griggs to race home and score.\nB6: Putting forth its highest-scoring frame of the day, Longwood scored five to break the deadlock. A pair of Lancers homers, a Jack McMullan solo shot and a Jae'den Carter three-run blast provided four of the five tallies.\nT7: Cutting into the Lancer lead, the Spartans pushed across a run as\nJohnny Sweeney\ncrossed as Longwood turned a double play.\nT8: Further trimming the Longwood advantage, Upstate scored twice in the seventh, getting an RBI single from Zenor and an RBI double from Sweeney.\nT9: Lifting a ball into center, Bentley picked up his third and final RBI of the day, scoring\nKenan Bowman\nwith a sac fly.\nUp Next for the Spartans\nWrapping its five-game road swing, USC Upstate travels to the Volunteer State next Tuesday for a midweek meeting with Tennessee. The Spartans and Volunteers meet for a 6 p.m. ET first pitch.\nConnect with the Spartans\nFacebook.com/UpstateAthletics\nTwitter | @UpstateBSB | @UpstateSpartans\nInstagram | @UpstateBSB | @UpstateSpartans\nYouTube.com/UpstateSpartans\nINVEST IN CHAMPIONS\n- Join the Upstate Athletic Fund (UAF) and enjoy enhanced benefits for your support of all USC Upstate programs! Make your gift today,\nclick here\n!",
